By Funmilola Gboteku Ikeja – An Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court on Thursday remanded a 40-year-old man, Joseph Banga, charged with defiling an underage. Chief Magistrate Olufunke Sule-Amzat, who did not take the defendant’s plea, ordered that he should be kept at the Kirikiri Prisons pending advice of the state Director of Public Prosecutions (DPP). Sule-Amzat ordered the police to send the case file to the DPP. She adjourned the case until July 22. The defendant, who lives at Orile Agege area of Lagos, is facing a count charge of defilement. Earlier, the prosecutor, ASP Benson Emuerhi, alleged  that the defendant unlawfully had carnal knowledge of a 14-year-old, at his residence. “The defendant defiled a 14-year-old, who lives around his area, by luring her into his apartment and  having carnal knowledge of her,” he said. Emuerhi said that the defendant was arrested after the teenager’s parents reported the case to the police. He noted that defilement  contravened Section 137 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015.